What do you mean? This:<p><pre><code>    var createItem = function(itemText) {
      return (
        <li>{itemText}</li>
      );
    };
    return (
      <ul>{this.props.items.map(createItem)}</ul>
    );
</code></pre>
...is clearly so much more logical than:<p><pre><code>    <ul><li>{{item}}</li></ul>
</code></pre>
Source: <a href="https://www.airpair.com/angularjs/posts/angular-vs-react-the-tie-breaker#1-9-templating" rel="nofollow">https://www.airpair.com/angularjs/posts/angular-vs-react-the...</a>
